---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Setup Guide — Worflo"
  description="How to connect Worflo to your HubSpot portal and start monitoring your workflows in under 60 seconds."
>
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 24px 80px">

    <p class="section-eyebrow">Setup Guide</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Getting started with Worflo</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--gray-5);font-size:15px;margin-bottom:48px">
      This guide walks you through connecting Worflo to your HubSpot portal. The full setup takes under 60 seconds and requires no developer access.
    </p>

    <div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--gray-7);line-height:1.8;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:40px">

      <!-- Requirements -->
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:12px">Before you start</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <li>A HubSpot account on the <strong>Professional or Enterprise</strong> plan (Workflows is not available on Starter)</li>
          <li>Admin or Super Admin access to your HubSpot portal</li>
          <li>A Worflo account — <a href="https://app.worflo.io/connect" style="color:var(--blue)">sign up free at app.worflo.io</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#0052cc;color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0">1</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin:0">Go to app.worflo.io/connect</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Open <a href="https://app.worflo.io/connect" style="color:var(--blue)">app.worflo.io/connect</a> in your browser. You'll see the Worflo connect screen with a "Connect HubSpot" button.</p>
        <div style="background:var(--gray-1);border-radius:8px;padding:16px 20px;margin-top:12px;font-size:13px;color:var(--gray-5)">
          If you're an invited team member (not the portal owner), click "Already a team member? Sign in →" and use your email and password instead.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#0052cc;color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0">2</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin:0">Click "Connect HubSpot"</h2>
        </div>
        <p>You'll be redirected to HubSpot's OAuth authorisation screen. Worflo requests the following permissions:</p>
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:12px 0;font-size:14px">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background:#f9fafb">
              <th style="padding:10px 14px;text-align:left;font-weight:600;border:1px solid #e5e7eb">Permission</th>
              <th style="padding:10px 14px;text-align:left;font-weight:600;border:1px solid #e5e7eb">Why it's needed</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb"><code>automation</code></td>
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb">Read your workflow definitions and execution history</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background:#f9fafb">
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb"><code>crm.objects.contacts.read</code></td>
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb">Look up contact properties for workflow simulation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb"><code>crm.objects.deals.read</code></td>
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb">Look up deal properties for workflow simulation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background:#f9fafb">
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb"><code>oauth</code></td>
              <td style="padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb">Authenticate and refresh your connection</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Worflo is <strong>read-only</strong> by default. The only write operation is the optional rollback feature, which requires your explicit confirmation.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#0052cc;color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0">3</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin:0">Approve the permissions</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Click <strong>Accept</strong> on the HubSpot permissions screen. You'll be redirected back to your Worflo dashboard automatically.</p>
        <div style="background:#f0fdf4;border-left:4px solid #00875a;border-radius:0 6px 6px 0;padding:14px 16px;margin-top:12px;font-size:14px;color:#065f46">
          You must be logged into the HubSpot portal you want to connect before clicking Accept. If you manage multiple portals, make sure you're in the right one first.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 4 -->
      <div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#0052cc;color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0">4</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin:0">Your workflows sync automatically</h2>
        </div>
        <p>After connecting, Worflo immediately kicks off a background sync. Within 1–2 minutes your workflows will appear on the <strong>Workflows</strong> page with their current status, version count, and error rate.</p>
        <p>Syncs run automatically every 5 minutes. Every time a workflow definition changes, a new version is saved and the change is recorded in the audit log.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 5 -->
      <div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#0052cc;color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0">5</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin:0">Set up error alerts (recommended)</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Go to <strong>Sidebar → Alerts</strong> and enter a notification email or Slack webhook URL. Worflo will notify you the moment a workflow errors so you don't find out from a customer.</p>
        <p>The error rate threshold slider lets you control sensitivity — set it to 10% to only alert when more than 1 in 10 executions are failing.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 6 -->
      <div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:14px">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#0052cc;color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0">6</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin:0">Invite your team (optional)</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Go to <strong>Sidebar → Team</strong> to invite colleagues. Choose their role:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;margin-top:8px">
          <li><strong>Admin</strong> — full access including billing and team management</li>
          <li><strong>Member</strong> — can view all data and use contact lookup</li>
          <li><strong>Viewer</strong> — read-only access to workflows and traces</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:12px">Invited members receive an email with a link to set their password. They log in at <a href="https://app.worflo.io/login" style="color:var(--blue)">app.worflo.io/login</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Troubleshooting -->
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--gray-3);padding-top:32px">
        <h2 style="font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:16px">Troubleshooting</h2>

        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px">
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:6px">No workflows appearing after connecting</h3>
            <p style="font-size:14px">Check that your HubSpot portal has active workflows under <strong>Automation → Workflows</strong>. Workflows must exist in the portal you connected. Wait up to 2 minutes for the first sync to complete.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:6px">OAuth error on the callback page</h3>
            <p style="font-size:14px">Make sure you start the connection from <a href="https://app.worflo.io/connect" style="color:var(--blue)">app.worflo.io/connect</a> — do not use a saved or bookmarked OAuth URL directly. If the error persists, try in an incognito window.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:6px">Traces not appearing</h3>
            <p style="font-size:14px">Execution traces only appear for runs that happen <em>after</em> you connected Worflo. Historical executions are not available. Make sure your workflows are active and have enrolled at least one contact since connecting.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:6px">HubSpot says "This app can't be installed"</h3>
            <p style="font-size:14px">Your HubSpot account must be on the Professional or Enterprise plan. Workflows (Automation) is not available on the Starter plan.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Support CTA -->
      <div style="background:var(--blue);border-radius:8px;padding:28px 32px;text-align:center;margin-top:8px">
        <p style="color:white;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px">Still stuck?</p>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.85);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px">Email us and we'll get back to you within one business day.</p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@worflo.io" style="display:inline-block;background:white;color:var(--blue);padding:10px 24px;border-radius:6px;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;text-decoration:none">hello@worflo.io</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
